data.enText: towards the sea; in the direction of the sea
the seaward side of the coastal road

simple_means.memory_skill: sea 海洋 + ward 向…，朝… → 向海（的）

tr: directed or situated away from inland regions and toward the sea or coast
example: from the hill he took a seaward course
on the seaward side of the road

tr: (of winds) coming from the sea toward the land
in the direction of the sea

value.boxr_value: The form seawards can also be used for meaning 1. seawards 也可用于义项1。

value.def: Something that moves or faces seaward or seawards moves or faces in the direction of the sea or further out to sea.

example.ex: A barge was about a hundred yards away, waiting to return seaward...
example.tran: 一艘驳船停在大约 100 码开外，等待着返海回航。

example.ex: It faced seawards to the north.

value.def: The seaward side of something faces in the direction of the sea or further out to sea.

example.ex: The houses on the seaward side of the road were all in ruins.
example.tran: 马路临海一侧的房子全部沦为废墟。

partsOfSpeech.dec: back 后边 + ward 向…，朝… → 向后（的）
down 向下 + ward 向…，朝… → 向下（的）
heaven 天 + ward 向…，朝… → 朝向天空（的）
home 家 + ward 向…，朝… → 向家（的）
in 在里面的 + ward 向…，朝… → 向内（的）
north 北 + ward 向…，朝… → 向北（的）
out 外面的 + ward 向…，朝… → 向外（的）
sea 海洋 + ward 向…，朝… → 向海（的）
up 向上 + ward 向…，朝… → 向上（的）
